Ceres: "Luna, you haven't changed at all since then. Straightforward, serious,

Ceres: "I see."
Ceres: "Luna, I haven't changed my personality either, have I?"

\C[23][Luna]\C[0] "I think you have changed a little, Lord Ceres. You're different from the Ceres

\C[23][Luna]\C[0] I think the Lord Ceres of the past was more of a slacker. Compared to before,

Ceres: I see...!

\C[23][Luna]\C[0] Lord Ceres, why does the Knights of Messiah interfere with other countries? Why
do you try to help other nations that have nothing to do with you? The Lord
Ceres of the past wouldn't have bothered with such troublesome matters.
Ceres: ...
Ceres: ...
Ceres: It's for the sake of a man who wished for true peace without resistance.
\C[23][Luna]\C[0] A man without resistance?

Ceres: The battle with Grales... During that war, various countries were
fighting over territories. It was an endless war where blood washed blood.

Ceres: But a certain person from a certain country tried to break the chain of
wars. They said, "Let's all stop this endless war." And so, that country ceased
to fight.

Ceres: Naturally, the country that gave up fighting unilaterally suffered
damage. Even so, a certain man from that country persisted in non-resistance and
did not fight back. Because of that, many of his countrymen died.

Ceres: In the end, that man even made graves for the enemy soldiers and
protected the citizens of the enemy nation while only defending against their
attacks.
\C[23][Luna]\C[0] Is this man without resistance Prince Reanu of the Kingdom of Ryubel...?
Ceres: ...

Ceres: Prince Reanu of Ryubel was once known as a skilled warrior who enjoyed
slaughter so much that even the great generals of Grales trembled at the mention
of his name.

Ceres: I asked Reanu many times. Why are you, of all people, just taking it? Why
do you, known for your demonic strength, persist in non-resistance? Even going
so far as to make graves for enemy soldiers killed by mistake by Ryubel's troops
and protecting their families.

Ceres: When I heard the answer from Reanu... when I heard 'the true answer' from
his mouth, I decided to inherit his will and do what he couldn't. That's when I
thought of creating the Knights of Messiah.
\C[23][Luna]\C[0] Lord Ceres...
Ceres: So, the Knights of Messiah are carrying on Prince Reanu's will?
\C[23][Luna]\C[0] Then, are the Knights of Messiah inheriting Prince Reanu's will?
Ceres: ...

Ceres: Haha... Sorry, for such a boring and long-winded story. I just end up
talking when it's with you, Luna.
Ceres: ...
Ceres: But... Reanu was wrong.
Ceres: Non-resistance doesn't work against opponents who won't listen to reason.
Ceres: I couldn't do anything for Reanu. I was powerless.
\C[23][Luna]\C[0] Lord Ceres...
Ceres: ...

Ceres: It's sad, but perhaps Lucia has become one of those 'opponents who won't

Ceres: But I'm holding onto a sliver of hope and thought about talking with
Lucia. I went to the gates of Jupiterino but was turned away spectacularly.
Haha...

Ceres: I don't have the power to move armies; I'm just a middle manager who

Ceres: The little that I can do is to first head to Jupiterino and investigate.

Ceres: Well then, I should be heading back soon.

bad wolf~
